            <section class="main-section empty" id="moderation">
                <header>
                    <h1>Moderation</h1>
                </header>
                <h2>Verification System</h2>
                <p>Set up a verification system<br>With Pogy you can create a verification system easily</p>
                <div class="code">
                    <code><span class="purple">1- </span>setverificationchannel #channel</code><br>
                    <code><span class="purple">2-</span> setverificationrole @role</code><br>
                    <code><span class="purple">3-</span> setverificationmessage &lt; message &gt;</code><br>

                </div>
                <p>Done!</b> Here is how you can set up a really easy verification system with Pogy!</p>
                <h2>Auto Role</h2>
                <p>This will automatically add the specified role every time a member joins the guild</p>
                <h2>Lock and Unlock Channel</h2>
                <p>This will easily lock the channel provided to stop grief, as you can unlock it anytime</p>
                <h2>Advanced Warning</h2>
                <p>When warning a user, you can use the Auto Kick Command which will auto kick every member with a certain number of warns, as you can also clear warns and check warn logs with its date and reason.
                </p>
                <h2>Advanced Logging</h2>
                <p>This feature includes: <br>- Deleted message logging<br>- Nickname Logging<br>- Edited messages Logging
                    <br>- Member Logging<br>- Role logging</p>
                <h2>Disable mentions</h2>
                <p>Are you that person that hates getting pinged, well the <b>Disable mentions</b> If enabled, this feature will delete every ping and automatically then warn the user that pinged you. This command is automatically disabled once you send
                    any message again in any channel</p>
                <h2>Leave &amp; Welcome Message</h2>
                <p>Set up both welcome and leave messages to your server easily</p>
                <h2>Ban &amp; Soft Ban</h2>
                <p>Ban a member from the server, then unban directly. This will delete all his messages</p>
                <h2>Purge</h2>
                <p>Delete the specified amount of messages from the provided channel, this feature can also be used with the command <b> Warn Purge </b></p>
                <h2>Other Commands</h2>
                <p>These commands include; setnickname, slowmode, mute, addrole, removerole</p>
